p.
  In practice, the only difference between the two types of observable
  is that properties have a current value. The process of subscribing
  to both types of observable is the same: you call the #[a(href='#on-value') onValue]
  method, passing to it a callback function. But when you subscribe
  to a property which has a current value, the callback is called
  immediately (synchronously) with the current value of the property.
